        "timestamp": "2023-06-30 13:17:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFor some reason the maven-verify Jenkins job for ccsdk/oran (‘london’ branch) seems to be using JDK 11 – and so failing. \nBut, as far as I can see the jjb file in ci-management defines that it should use “openjdk17”\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=ci-management.git;a=blob;f=jjb/ccsdk/ccsdk-oran.yaml#l34 (line 34)\nSo I have no idea why this is happening.\n\nNote also: \nAll ccsdk-oran-maven-verify-<branchname>-mvn38-openjdk17 Jenkins jobs seem to have disappeared. \nI note that ccsdk-oran-maven-verify-london-mvn38-openjdk17/5 ran correctly on June 26 in change ccsdk/oran/+/135168\nBut I don’t see any change in ci-management/jjb/ccsdk that could have caused that \n… or maybe I’m missing something? \n(Maybe its related to this change: https://jenkins.onap.org/view/ci-management/job/ci-management-jjb-merge/3381/changes)?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
